tips.text: Yeah sure it's authentic. But where's the bread that greets you when you place an order? You wait with a glass of water... A bit pricey but better than some other Italian place. Try daily specials.
Great Italian food.....!

formattedAddress: 396 Upper Bukit Timah Rd (The Rail Mall)

tips.text: Great prata, teh tarik ice a bit too sweet, but expected from Indian restaurant. Not too crowded. Quick service. Masala chicken is big portion!
The lady boss and the staffs are all Koreans. Authentic, as native Korean families go there for their meals! Their fried chicken is very moist and tender (psst, even the chicken breast!)👍
Come try at this chicken barn yard decor eatery only when you are free & have patience to wait... Feeling so sleepy after over-dosed of generous portion of fried stuff.

tips.text: The chicken rice here is so so. Food is served not as I thought. Service wise, the service crews are generally polite. For the price you are paying, perhaps it is decent and cheap.
